From: Marian Chereji <marian.chereji@freescale.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Feb 2012 00:44:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 091/518] Bad order of arguments in xx layer macro

The non-debug versions of xx_malloc_smart and xx_zalloc_smart macros
from the DPA compatibility layer are feeding the arguments to the
function dpa_offld_malloc_smart in the wrong order.

Signed-off-by: Mihai Serb <mihai.serb@freescale.com>
[Grabbed from the branch, LINUX_IR5.2.0, of
https://git.freescale.com/git-private/cgit.cgi/ppc/alu-b4860/linux.git.]
Signed-off-by: Tiejun Chen <tiejun.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/dpa_compat.h |    6 +++---
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/dpa_compat.h b/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/dpa_compat.h
index 32f5588..2c57e04 100644
--- a/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/dpa_compat.h
+++ b/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/dpa_compat.h
@@ -100,14 +100,14 @@
 #define xx_malloc_smart(size, \
 			mem_partition_id, \
 			alignment) \
-	dpa_offld_malloc_smart(size, 0, mem_partition_id, alignment)
+	dpa_offld_malloc_smart(size, mem_partition_id, alignment, 0)
 #define xx_zalloc_smart(size, \
 			mem_partition_id, \
 			alignment) \
 	dpa_offld_malloc_smart(size, \
-			1, \
 			mem_partition_id, \
-			alignment)
+			alignment, \
+			1)
 #define xx_free_smart				dpa_offld_free_smart
 #define xx_display_mem_leaks()
 
